parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake can cause a loss of stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The rear brake has little to no stopping power
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has to be pumped multiple times to stop
the brake system requires frequent bleeding
the brake system fails to hold the bike on a hill
a snapping noise is heard when the brake fails.
